<br>
I also don't want to get rid of my spell animations... that's one of the things that annoys me about champions.  I want to look just like a spellcaster when I'm casting spells, because that has uses too.<br>
<br>
I have no particularly affiliation with death or souls, so Feign Death and Lifedrain don't seem to really fit.  Feign Death wouldn't work very well unless it stopped people from swinging at you (broke auto-attack).  The day that people found out we could Feign Death, they'd be stabbing every rogue-looking corpse that they see.<br>
<br>
I have weapon styles to control aggro, I don't really need a spell for it.<br>
<br>
I also don't need an illusory attack to take down bladeturn, my PA opening does that just fine.<br>
<br>
I like the Charged Blade idea... I think a one-time magical bonus to damage would be very handy, especially if we could cast it between fights on multi-pulls when I don't have enough time to apply a poison.<br>
<br>
I don't want a pet, but I like the short duration &quot;illusory me&quot; distraction castable on a ground target.<br>
<br>
Blur Mind allows bypassing of content, and would require a change to how places are designed.  I don't want it, and I doubt we ever see anything even remotely like it.  The class that gets this becomes &quot;necessary&quot; for any travelling group, regardless of what else they can do.<br>
<br>
Gather Shadows, Elude Pursuit... that's why I have Stealth.  No need for them.<br>
<br>
Shadow Speed would be awesome.<br>
<br>
I want Confusion in a bad way.  In the right circumstances it's very powerful, and I think it fits well with the Nightshade theme.<br>
<br>
Blinding Light... heh, rogues with mesmerize.  If it had even a 10 second duration, we'd be freakishly more powerful than we are now.  Not going to happen, and probably just as well. <p><b>Ciardha Sidhe</b>, Elven Nightshade of Guinevere<br><small>Explorer 93% | Killer 60% | Socializer 40% | Achiever 6%</small><br><i>"You killed a little dwarf.  You brute."</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uciardhasidhe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ciardha Sidhe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 11:57:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2085.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.starseer.com/nightshade/ciardha60a.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nightshade Spell Ideas (Long)</span><hr size=1> Just for amusement, here's a list of spells I proposed a while ago, back when Huff made the general request.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Veil Step</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - A spell that puts you into stealth regardless of enemies around you or combat timer. Casting time less than 2 seconds. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Glamour of the Fey</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - A very short stun (duration ~3 seconds), instant casting that doesn't break stealth, long timer. It's primary use is to keep things from walking away right when we strike, but obviously useful other times as well.  (Changes to stun functionality make this unwanted in RvR, and it lessens the power of Creeping Death so no longer such a useful thing.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Will o' the Wisp</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - A very long range bolt spell (approximately twice our DD range), appears as a small bobbing light, hits target for negligible damage, casting time 1 second. Used to break opponent stealth, disrupt spellcasting, disrupt archers.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Wail of the Baensidhe</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Point blank AE stun, small radius (melee distance), instant casting, very long timer (no chain-stunning). This would be our getaway spell, no need for a sprint-like spell. (Obsolete now that a single add doesn't guarantee death.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Brighid's Gift</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Ranged spell, targets enemy players, AE effect. Lights all of their torches.  Can be cast on ground target. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Annwyn's Blessing</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Self-only buff. Doubles chance of getting a critical hit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uphaelondaoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phaelon DAoC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 12:12:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2085.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nightshade Spell Ideas (Long)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> As a healer, it's quite a shock to play a class that has nothing to contribute to a group but hassles. I know well how it works. Nice group, Tank, me, some other damage dealers etc. We invite a Shadowblade, and he either doesn't backstab (I use this term generically for the high damage hidden styles), or he does, and I end up having to 'emergency heal' him, which causes me to get the aggro myself. I remember once thanking a Shadowblade for not getting aggro, and I realize now that I was thanking him for not using the defining ability of his class!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
