</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=makalu>Makalu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 6:54:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2085.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nightshade Spell Ideas (Long)</span><hr size=1> Ok, I guess these weren't very popular ideas, but let me clear up a few misconceptions, probably caused by a poor explanation.<br>
<br>
I don't want to get rid of spell animations... I want to get rid of spell SOUNDS.  I'm all for body movements, gestures, etc.  What I want to change about the graphics is the bright swirling, attention getting lights.  The current DD spell is actually pretty good in this respect.<br>
<br>
You say your PA opening takes down a bladeturn... but doesn't the bladeturn stop the damage of this attack?  True, your followups will get through, but letting that first one get through was my intent.<br>
<br>
The theurgist pet's are not true pets.  I can't really add much to my description of them... but it's more of a DoT that has a physical form and can be targeted and take damage.  Try a theurgist to level 5 sometime, it's a very 'different' class.  Your idea of being able to cast it at a ground target is good... it'd just stand there, maybe for a longer period than if it's cast at a target?<br>
<br>
Blur Mind... you're probably right.  Stealthers can already bypass content, but allowing diverse groups to do it would be a bit much.<br>
<br>
My intention for Blinding Light was more for a stun duration mezz... 3 seconds, just long enough for you to strafe around to the back or side and hit a style.  It's just for soloing, to allow you to put those side/back styles to use.  Probably not a concern, because there are so many styles available to you that you don't need to use those.  A normal stun is more straightforward, but I was trying to balance it by making you trade something off... if you want to use it, you have to stop attacking for a time.<br>
<br>
<br>
